Procedure.description:
PROCEDURE PURPOSE: to execute the SAM to FPM transition.
PROCEDURE VERSION: 7.0 RESPONSIBILITY: Arturo Del Foco LAST MODIFIED DATE: 16.11.2022
CHANGE HISTORY: Version 7.0 (AdF - 16.11.2022) Change History: - EUM/MTG/AR/5479: corrected message at variable interaction step P.5.A6; - AIM 212092 and EUM/MTG/AR/5108: due to TM bandwidth limitations, added call to N_PUS_0003 to disable TM_003_025_HKTM_MT_PF_AOCS_SKM_ATT_QTN_01_EUM (SID 10802) before start of procedure N_SYS_0035; - Procedure Description aligned to EUMETSAT template.
PROCEDURE OBJECTIVES: This procedure is used to: - check the Pre-conditions applicable to MTG-I satellites prior to the execution of the transition from SAQ/SAM to NOM/FPM - perform a transition from SAQ/SAM to NOM/FPM
PROCEDURE OVERVIEW: The basic scheme of the procedure is: <> Confirm Pre-conditions OK (N_SYS_I035) <> If the Pre-conditions are OK: (N_SYS_0035) - Upload all needed TCs to the MTL - Wait for transition from SAM to GAM - Wait for OOP initialisation, update and activation - Wait for transition from GAM to SKM - Wait for transition from SAQ to NOM - Enable Ranging for Orbit Determination
PROCEDURE PRE-CONDITIONS: TBW
PROCEDURE CONSTRAINTS (1) The procedure assumes that the Payload is in SURVIVAL mode from the start to the end as it is expected in SAT SAQ and AOCS SAM. (2) It is highly recommended not to execute other commanding activities during the complete duration of the procedure. (3) The transition from SAM to GAM shall not be executed if the spin rate of the satellite is SAM is higher than 0.4 degrees/second (see chapter 4.2.2.1 of MTG-OHB-PF-MA-0024) (4) !!! All TCs existing in the MTL at the beginning of execution of the procedure are deleted. (5) The first GAM profile needs to have a duration of 1200 seconds.
SPACECRAFT CONFIGURATION Start of Procedure: - SAT mode: SAQ - AOCS mode: SAM (with spin rate <= 0.4 degrees/s) - AOCS S/S: nominal configuration for SAM (with STRs and RWs already ON) - DHS S/S: nominal configuration - TTC S/S: nominal configuration - EPS S/S: nominal configuration - PDD S/S: OFF - TCS S/S: nominal configuration - UPS S/S: nominal configuration - FCI mode: SURVIVAL (i.e. survival thermal control active) - LI mode: SURVIVAL (i.e. survival thermal control active)
End of Procedure: - SAT mode: NOM - AOCS mode: FPM - AOCS S/S: nominal configuration for FPM (with APC disabled) - DHS S/S: nominal configuration - TTC S/S: nominal configuration (+ Ranging ON) - EPS S/S: nominal configuration - PDD S/S: OFF - TCS S/S: nominal configuration - UPS S/S: nominal configuration - FCI mode: SURVIVAL (i.e. survival thermal control active) - LI mode: SURVIVAL (i.e. survival thermal control active)
GROUND SEGMENT CONFIGURATION: TBW

step.title: Info on THL dumps during SM recovery

StepBody.message: This is the second dump of the THL executed during the SM recovery. It covers the data between times: from time of the first dump (at Step P.2) until now (after the completion of the RWOL, nominally with the satellite in SAQ/SAM/RWSA).
